{"parentUuid":"155533ef-79d7-4c87-89fd-fb75b5848e5a","isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/nateusher/workbench","sessionId":"3cd96871-fb4b-41c1-9ba9-9fa251bcb3be","version":"2.1.55","gitBranch":"main","agentId":"a47544cd14311bfc5","slug":"tingly-gliding-shore","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01JSASULSmWA3eW2haHjpBbo","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Based on my research, I now have a comprehensive understanding of Claude Code hooks. Let me summarize the findings:\n\n## Research Summary: Claude Code Hooks\n\nI've researched Claude Code hooks by examining the official documentation. Here's what I found:\n\n### Hook Events Available\n\nClaude Code supports these hook events, with the key ones for post-execution being:\n\n**Post-Execution Events (fires AFTER an action completes):**\n- **`PostToolUse`** - Fires after a tool call succeeds (e.g., after Bash command completes, after file edits). Can't undo the action since it already executed.\n- **`PostToolUseFailure`** - Fires after a tool call fails\n- **`Stop`** - Fires whenever Claude finishes responding (not just at task completion, but at every turn)\n\n**Pre-Execution Events (fires BEFORE an action executes):**\n- **`PreToolUse`** - Fires before any tool call (Bash, Edit, Write, Read, etc.). Can block the action by exiting with code 2.\n\n**Other Lifecycle Events:**\n- `SessionStart` - Session begins/resumes\n- `UserPromptSubmit` - When you submit a prompt\n- `PermissionRequest` - Permission dialog appears\n- `Notification` - Claude needs attention\n- `SubagentStart` / `SubagentStop` - Subagent lifecycle\n- `TaskCompleted` - Task marked as completed\n- `InstructionsLoaded` - CLAUDE.md files loaded\n- `ConfigChange` - Configuration files change\n- `PreCompact` / `SessionEnd` - Session lifecycle\n\n### How Hooks Work\n\n1. **Configuration Locations:**\n   - `~/.claude/settings.json` - Global, all projects\n   - `.claude/settings.json` - Project-specific, shareable\n   - `.claude/settings.local.json` - Project-specific, not shared (gitignored)\n   - Via `/hooks` interactive menu (CLI command)\n\n2. **Hook Types:**\n   - **Command hooks** (`\"type\": \"command\"`) - Runs shell commands\n   - **HTTP hooks** (`\"type\": \"http\"`) - POSTs to HTTP endpoint\n   - **Prompt hooks** (`\"type\": \"prompt\"`) - Single LLM call for yes/no decisions\n   - **Agent hooks** (`\"type\": \"agent\"`) - Multi-turn subagent for complex verification\n\n3. **Input/Output Format:**\n   - Hooks receive JSON on stdin with context about the event\n   - Common fields: `session_id`, `cwd`, `hook_event_name`, `tool_name`, `tool_input`\n   - Exit codes control behavior:\n     - **Exit 0** - Allow action (stdout can contain context injection or JSON decisions)\n     - **Exit 2** - Block action (stderr message fed to Claude as feedback)\n     - **Other** - Allow action, log to stderr\n\n4. **Matchers (Filtering):**\n   - Filter hooks to specific tools/events using regex patterns\n   - Example: `\"matcher\": \"Edit|Write\"` runs only on file edits\n   - MCP tools use format: `mcp__<server>__<tool>` (e.g., `mcp__github__.*`)\n\n### Current User Settings\n\nYour configuration files at `/Users/nateusher/.claude/`:\n- **settings.json** - Contains global settings (model: \"opus\", plugins, permissions, env vars) but NO hooks currently configured\n- **settings.local.json** - Contains permissions but NO hooks configured\n- **No hooks directory** exists yet\n\n### Documentation References\n\nThe complete reference documentation for hooks is at:\n- **Full Hook Reference:** https://code.claude.com/docs/en/hooks.md (full event schemas, JSON formats, async hooks, HTTP hooks, prompt hooks)\n- **Hooks Guide:** https://code.claude.com/docs/en/hooks-guide.md (practical examples: auto-format code, block edits, notifications, audit logging)\n\n### Key Insights\n\n- **`PostToolUse` with Bash matcher** would let you run code after every Bash command executes\n- **`PreToolUse` with Bash matcher** would let you validate/block Bash commands before they run\n- Hooks run in **parallel** when multiple match, with identical commands **automatically deduplicated**\n- Hooks can inject context back into Claude via stdout (on exit 0) or block actions with stderr (exit 2)\n- **10-minute timeout** by default, configurable per hook\n- Your user-level settings are at `~/.claude/settings.json`; project-level at `.claude/settings.json`"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":6,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1561,"cache_read_input_tokens":33007,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1561,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":4,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"}},"requestId":"req_011CYky6r6Q8vYTnXbQMiMAY","type":"assistant","uuid":"604872c3-fbd2-4891-91ca-148ad341e6b0","timestamp":"2026-03-06T01:35:38.657Z"}
